    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen deleting lines of text with diagnostics at bottom, `Invalid 'line': out of range` will be thrown in `CursorMoved` autocommand, from `runtime/lua/vim/diagnostic.lua:1605`.\nI've confirmed that this problem is LSP-independent, tested on multiple servers (`clangd`, `denols` and `csharpls` currently) and they all have the same behavior.\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/356b0a41-98fa-4765-aa3e-ecb5e340c5ac)\nHere is a screenshot that I made some errors in a CSharp file and then `gg=G` to delete all text.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nSetup some LSP and setup diagnostics virtual text with\n```lua\nvim.diagnostic.config {\n    virtual_text = { prefix = icons.ui.VirtualPrefix, current_line = false },\n    update_in_insert = true,\n    underline = true,\n    severity_sort = true,\n}\n```\nAnd create a buffer with the LSP enabled, create some diagnostic messages and `ggdG` to delete all text.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe text should be deleted without any error, of course.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-398+ga87aa68ed0\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nthat feature doesn't exist in vim at all\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux onion27-archlinux 6.14.6-arch1-1 #1 SMP PREEMPT_DYNAMIC Fri, 09 May 2025 17:36:18 +0000 x86_64 GNU/Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nwezterm 20250511-222309-475e9f57\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\n`neovim-git` from AUR, fresh build just at the moment before I creating the issue and reproduced it one more time",
